        "pg_page_low_003_iana_reserved_0037"
      ],
      "text": "There is additionally a Special-Use Domain Names registry documenting special-use domains designated by technical standards. For further information, see Special-Use Domain Names (RFC 6761).\nRoot Zone Management\nTop-Level Domains\nFiles and Downloads\nManage Delegations\nInstructions & Guides\nRegister/modify an .INT domain\nIDN Practices Repository\nRoot Key Signing Key (DNSSEC)\nTrust Anchors and Rollovers\nKey Signing Ceremonies\nPolicies & Procedures\nCommunity Representatives\nReserved Domains\nRoot Zone Registry\nNumber Resources\nAbuse Information\nProtocol Registries\nTime Zone Database\nThe IANA functions coordinate the Internet’s globally unique identifiers, and are provided by Public Technical Identifiers , an affiliate of ICANN .\nTerms of Service",
      "tokenEstimate": 187
    }
